1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,990
Blizzard hit Wisconsin at 11:00 p.m.

2
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:04,350
like it wanted to destroy something.

3
00:00:04,360 --> 00:00:07,470
Wind screaming, snow sideways, -15 with

4
00:00:07,480 --> 00:00:08,790
wind chill.

5
00:00:08,800 --> 00:00:10,630
Connor couldn't sleep.

6
00:00:10,640 --> 00:00:13,150
6 years old, wired, listening to the

7
00:00:13,160 --> 00:00:14,710
house groan.

8
00:00:14,720 --> 00:00:16,470
We were crashing in my parents guest

9
00:00:16,480 --> 00:00:18,590
room. 2 months since I lost my job and

10
00:00:18,600 --> 00:00:20,550
the apartment that came with it.

11
00:00:20,560 --> 00:00:23,350
Air mattress for him, cot for me, house

12
00:00:23,360 --> 00:00:25,030
rules that said we were tolerated, not

13
00:00:25,040 --> 00:00:26,710
welcome.

14
00:00:26,720 --> 00:00:29,070
"Need water." He whispered.

15
00:00:29,080 --> 00:00:30,350
"Okay."

16
00:00:30,360 --> 00:00:32,030
"Quiet, though."

17
00:00:32,040 --> 00:00:34,110
We crept downstairs.

18
00:00:34,120 --> 00:00:35,790
I turned on the smallest light over the

19
00:00:35,800 --> 00:00:36,990
sink.

20
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:38,910
Filled a glass halfway, handed it to

21
00:00:38,920 --> 00:00:39,910
him.

22
00:00:39,920 --> 00:00:42,110
He took it with both hands, careful like

23
00:00:42,120 --> 00:00:43,470
I'd taught him.

24
00:00:43,480 --> 00:00:45,230
Turned to go back.

25
00:00:45,240 --> 00:00:47,430
His elbow caught the shelf.

26
00:00:47,440 --> 00:00:49,190
The narrow one mounted between kitchen

27
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:50,630
and hallway.

28
00:00:50,640 --> 00:00:52,030
The one holding my younger brother

29
00:00:52,040 --> 00:00:54,830
Kyle's Harvard Law acceptance trophy.

30
00:00:54,840 --> 00:00:56,150
It tipped.

31
00:00:56,160 --> 00:00:57,950
Connor grabbed for it.

32
00:00:57,960 --> 00:00:59,470
Missed.

33
00:00:59,480 --> 00:01:01,470
Trophy hit the floor, glass base

34
00:01:01,480 --> 00:01:03,430
shattering across tile.

35
00:01:03,440 --> 00:01:05,189
Connor froze.

36
00:01:05,199 --> 00:01:07,270
The cup slipped from his hands, water

37
00:01:07,280 --> 00:01:09,470
spilling into the glass shards.

38
00:01:09,480 --> 00:01:11,630
"Oh, no." He whispered.

39
00:01:11,640 --> 00:01:13,550
"Oh, no. Oh, no."

40
00:01:13,560 --> 00:01:15,790
"It's okay." I said, already moving for

41
00:01:15,800 --> 00:01:17,350
paper towels.

42
00:01:17,360 --> 00:01:18,630
"Accident.

43
00:01:18,640 --> 00:01:20,110
We'll clean it up."

44
00:01:20,120 --> 00:01:21,990
Footsteps upstairs.

45
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:23,430
"Fast."

46
00:01:23,440 --> 00:01:25,070
My mother's voice carried down before

47
00:01:25,080 --> 00:01:26,510
she appeared.

48
00:01:26,520 --> 00:01:28,070
"What did you break?"

49
00:01:28,080 --> 00:01:30,310
She came down in her robe, face already

50
00:01:30,320 --> 00:01:31,790
set in that expression that meant I'd

51
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:34,390
confirmed every low expectation.

52
00:01:34,400 --> 00:01:36,550
My father Richard followed slower,

53
00:01:36,560 --> 00:01:37,790
heavier.

54
00:01:37,800 --> 00:01:39,350
My mother Carol stopped at the bottom

55
00:01:39,360 --> 00:01:40,470
step.

56
00:01:40,480 --> 00:01:42,510
Saw the shattered trophy.

57
00:01:42,520 --> 00:01:44,310
Hand to her mouth.

58
00:01:44,320 --> 00:01:45,830
"Do you know how hard Kyle worked for

59
00:01:45,840 --> 00:01:46,870
that?"

60
00:01:46,880 --> 00:01:48,670
Her voice climbing.

61
00:01:48,680 --> 00:01:50,990
"Do you know what that represented?"

62
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:52,990
Connor started crying.

63
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:55,310
The silent kind where his body shook,

64
00:01:55,320 --> 00:01:57,750
but barely any sound came out.

65
00:01:57,760 --> 00:01:59,470
"It was an accident." I said, kneeling

66
00:01:59,480 --> 00:02:01,150
to pick up glass.

67
00:02:01,160 --> 00:02:02,630
"He's 6."

68
00:02:02,640 --> 00:02:04,310
"You never taught him to be careful." My

69
00:02:04,320 --> 00:02:06,390
father said from the doorway. "Just like

70
00:02:06,400 --> 00:02:07,990
you never learned."

71
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:09,910
"He bumped a shelf." I kept my voice

72
00:02:09,920 --> 00:02:11,029
level.

73
00:02:11,039 --> 00:02:13,030
"Kids bump things."

74
00:02:13,040 --> 00:02:15,150
My mother's face twisted.

75
00:02:15,160 --> 00:02:16,830
"Not in our house."

76
00:02:16,840 --> 00:02:19,070
"Kyle was never this careless."

77
00:02:19,080 --> 00:02:21,190
"Kyle's 22 and at Harvard." I said

78
00:02:21,200 --> 00:02:23,190
before I could stop myself. "Connor's

79
00:02:23,200 --> 00:02:24,390
6."

80
00:02:24,400 --> 00:02:26,150
Wrong thing to say.

81
00:02:26,160 --> 00:02:28,310
My father's jaw tightened.

82
00:02:28,320 --> 00:02:30,910
"You're right. It's not the same.

83
00:02:30,920 --> 00:02:33,150
Kyle earned his place here.

84
00:02:33,160 --> 00:02:34,630
You're on our couch because you couldn't

85
00:02:34,640 --> 00:02:36,070
keep a job."

86
00:02:36,080 --> 00:02:37,510
There it was.

87
00:02:37,520 --> 00:02:39,150
"I got laid off."

88
00:02:39,160 --> 00:02:41,150
"The whole third shift did."

89
00:02:41,160 --> 00:02:43,030
"You got a girl pregnant at 18." My

90
00:02:43,040 --> 00:02:45,190
father continued like I hadn't spoken.

91
00:02:45,200 --> 00:02:48,270
"Dropped out. Burned every opportunity.

92
00:02:48,280 --> 00:02:49,670
Now you're raising a kid who breaks

93
00:02:49,680 --> 00:02:51,830
things in the middle of the night."

94
00:02:51,840 --> 00:02:53,790
Connor sobbed louder.

95
00:02:53,800 --> 00:02:56,190
"I'm sorry." He kept saying.

96
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:58,350
I put my hand on his shoulder.

97
00:02:58,360 --> 00:03:00,150
"Not your fault, buddy."

98
00:03:00,160 --> 00:03:01,870
"Don't tell him it's not his fault." My

99
00:03:01,880 --> 00:03:03,630
mother snapped. "He needs to learn

100
00:03:03,640 --> 00:03:05,270
consequences."

101
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:07,990
"He's 6." I repeated. "It's 11:00 p.m.

102
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:09,950
during a blizzard. Can we handle this in

103
00:03:09,960 --> 00:03:11,430
the morning?"

104
00:03:11,440 --> 00:03:13,430
My father stepped closer.

105
00:03:13,440 --> 00:03:14,750
Voice cold.

106
00:03:14,760 --> 00:03:15,750
"No.

107
00:03:15,760 --> 00:03:17,390
We're handling this now.

108
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:18,750
Because I'm done.

109
00:03:18,760 --> 00:03:20,110
We're done."

110
00:03:20,120 --> 00:03:21,710
My stomach dropped.

111
00:03:21,720 --> 00:03:22,990
"Done with what?"

112
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:24,190
"This."

113
00:03:24,200 --> 00:03:26,070
He gestured at Connor, at me, at the

114
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:27,550
broken glass.

115
00:03:27,560 --> 00:03:29,510
"We opened our home, and this is what we

116
00:03:29,520 --> 00:03:32,630
get. Chaos. Disrespect." "It was an

117
00:03:32,640 --> 00:03:33,910
accident."

118
00:03:33,920 --> 00:03:35,710
"Your trash kid has no place here." My

119
00:03:35,720 --> 00:03:37,870
father said. Clean and final like he'd

120
00:03:37,880 --> 00:03:39,910
been waiting weeks to say it.

121
00:03:39,920 --> 00:03:41,750
Silence except for wind and Connor's

122
00:03:41,760 --> 00:03:43,230
hitching breaths.

123
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:45,470
"Richard." My mother said. But didn't

124
00:03:45,480 --> 00:03:46,910
say stop.

125
00:03:46,920 --> 00:03:49,070
"We're done raising your mistake.

126
00:03:49,080 --> 00:03:50,550
Get out."

127
00:03:50,560 --> 00:03:53,510
Connor looked up at me, eyes huge.

128
00:03:53,520 --> 00:03:56,350
"It's -15 outside." I said.

129
00:03:56,360 --> 00:03:57,910
"Blizzard warning."

130
00:03:57,920 --> 00:03:59,990
"Should have thought about that."

131
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:01,870
My father grabbed two duffel bags from

132
00:04:01,880 --> 00:04:04,470
the closet, threw them at my feet.

133
00:04:04,480 --> 00:04:05,590
"Pack.

134
00:04:05,600 --> 00:04:07,070
Now."

135
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:09,150
My mother crossed her arms.

136
00:04:09,160 --> 00:04:11,350
"You can't keep manipulating us, Ethan.

137
00:04:11,360 --> 00:04:13,270
We've sacrificed enough."

138
00:04:13,280 --> 00:04:14,990
"I lost my job.

139
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:16,910
That's not manipulation."

140
00:04:16,920 --> 00:04:18,590
"Get your things."

141
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:21,229
Connor grabbed my leg, shaking.

142
00:04:21,239 --> 00:04:22,670
"Are we leaving?"

143
00:04:22,680 --> 00:04:25,190
"Yeah, buddy. Get your coat."

144
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:27,190
My father watched while I shoved clothes

145
00:04:27,200 --> 00:04:28,590
into bags.

146
00:04:28,600 --> 00:04:30,550
Connor's bear, school folder,

147
00:04:30,560 --> 00:04:32,030
toothbrushes.

148
00:04:32,040 --> 00:04:33,590
The whole time standing in the doorway

149
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:35,230
making sure we didn't take anything that

150
00:04:35,240 --> 00:04:36,710
wasn't ours.

151
00:04:36,720 --> 00:04:38,230
At the front door, my mother held out

152
00:04:38,240 --> 00:04:39,470
her hand.

153
00:04:39,480 --> 00:04:41,070
"I'll take your key."

154
00:04:41,080 --> 00:04:43,190
I twisted it off my key ring, dropped it

155
00:04:43,200 --> 00:04:44,510
in her palm.

156
00:04:44,520 --> 00:04:46,750
She closed her fist around it. My father

157
00:04:46,760 --> 00:04:48,230
opened the door.

158
00:04:48,240 --> 00:04:50,350
Cold punched in, snow blowing into the

159
00:04:50,360 --> 00:04:51,590
hallway.

160
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:53,230
Connor whimpered.

161
00:04:53,240 --> 00:04:55,270
"Daddy, it's cold."

162
00:04:55,280 --> 00:04:57,510
I crouched down, zipped his coat tight,

163
00:04:57,520 --> 00:04:58,950
pulled his hood.

164
00:04:58,960 --> 00:05:00,830
"We're going to be okay."

165
00:05:00,840 --> 00:05:02,750
"Please." I said.

166
00:05:02,760 --> 00:05:04,590
"Just let us stay tonight.

167
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:06,110
We'll leave in the morning. It's

168
00:05:06,120 --> 00:05:07,470
dangerous."

169
00:05:07,480 --> 00:05:08,870
"You should have thought about that." My

170
00:05:08,880 --> 00:05:10,550
mother said, staring at the broken

171
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:11,750
trophy.

172
00:05:11,760 --> 00:05:13,830
"Out." My father said.

173
00:05:13,840 --> 00:05:16,030
I picked up both bags, took Connor's

174
00:05:16,040 --> 00:05:18,630
hand. Walked onto the porch.

175
00:05:18,640 --> 00:05:20,150
Door slammed.

176
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:21,710
Lock clicked.

177
00:05:21,720 --> 00:05:24,110
Connor started crying for real now.

178
00:05:24,120 --> 00:05:25,630
Full sobs.

179
00:05:25,640 --> 00:05:27,150
He looked at the wet spot on his sleeve

180
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:28,430
and whispered.

181
00:05:28,440 --> 00:05:30,070
"It's my fault."

182
00:05:30,080 --> 00:05:31,750
I knelt in the snow.

183
00:05:31,760 --> 00:05:32,790
"No.

184
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:34,510
This is not your fault.

185
00:05:34,520 --> 00:05:35,710
You hear me?

186
00:05:35,720 --> 00:05:37,070
Never."

187
00:05:37,080 --> 00:05:39,270
He nodded, but didn't believe me.

188
00:05:39,280 --> 00:05:41,150
My car was half buried.

189
00:05:41,160 --> 00:05:43,070
I threw bags in back, buckled Connor

190
00:05:43,080 --> 00:05:44,350
into his seat.

191
00:05:44,360 --> 00:05:46,430
Got in front, turned the key.

192
00:05:46,440 --> 00:05:47,590
Nothing.

193
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:48,990
Battery cold.

194
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:50,790
Dashboard lit up weak.

195
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:51,910
"Come on."

196
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:53,270
Tried again.

197
00:05:53,280 --> 00:05:55,390
Engine coughed, caught.

198
00:05:55,400 --> 00:05:57,390
Heater blasted cold air.

199
00:05:57,400 --> 00:05:58,950
Checked my phone.

200
00:05:58,960 --> 00:06:01,030
32% battery.

201
00:06:01,040 --> 00:06:03,750
$287 in my account.

202
00:06:03,760 --> 00:06:06,270
Cheapest motel nearby was 95 a night

203
00:06:06,280 --> 00:06:08,350
with reviews about bed bugs.

204
00:06:08,360 --> 00:06:09,830
Did the math.

205
00:06:09,840 --> 00:06:12,350
Motel tonight, maybe tomorrow.

206
00:06:12,360 --> 00:06:13,910
Then what?

207
00:06:13,920 --> 00:06:16,190
Police station crossed my mind.

208
00:06:16,200 --> 00:06:18,790
Small town, always staffed, warm,

209
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:20,950
public, witnesses.

210
00:06:20,960 --> 00:06:23,350
"Where are we going?" Connor asked.

211
00:06:23,360 --> 00:06:24,950
"Somewhere safe."

212
00:06:24,960 --> 00:06:26,430
"Are we in trouble?"

213
00:06:26,440 --> 00:06:28,830
"No, buddy. Grown-ups who lock kids out

214
00:06:28,840 --> 00:06:30,830
in blizzards are in trouble."

215
00:06:30,840 --> 00:06:32,430
He went quiet.

216
00:06:32,440 --> 00:06:35,390
Drove 4 miles at 20 miles per hour.

217
00:06:35,400 --> 00:06:37,670
Visibility maybe 20 feet.

218
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:39,910
Car slid twice, my stomach dropping

219
00:06:39,920 --> 00:06:41,590
before tires caught.

220
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:44,430
Connor held his bear, didn't speak.

221
00:06:44,440 --> 00:06:45,990
Police station was a small brick

222
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:47,950
building, lights on.

223
00:06:47,960 --> 00:06:49,430
I pulled in.

224
00:06:49,440 --> 00:06:51,030
"Why are we at the police?" Connor

225
00:06:51,040 --> 00:06:54,230
asked. "Because it's warm and safe.

226
00:06:54,240 --> 00:06:55,790
And when grown-ups make bad choices,

227
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:57,430
police need to know."

228
00:06:57,440 --> 00:07:00,150
We went inside. Heat hit hard.

229
00:07:00,160 --> 00:07:02,790
Desk sergeant behind plexiglass.

230
00:07:02,800 --> 00:07:05,630
Older guy, nameplate said Davies.

231
00:07:05,640 --> 00:07:07,350
He saw Connor shivering and his face

232
00:07:07,360 --> 00:07:08,630
changed.

233
00:07:08,640 --> 00:07:10,110
"Can I help you?

234
00:07:10,120 --> 00:07:11,550
Got locked out?

235
00:07:11,560 --> 00:07:13,350
Need somewhere warm?"

236
00:07:13,360 --> 00:07:15,630
He stood up, came around.

237
00:07:15,640 --> 00:07:17,070
"How old is he?"

238
00:07:17,080 --> 00:07:19,270
"6." Officer Davies' expression

239
00:07:19,280 --> 00:07:20,550
tightened.

240
00:07:20,560 --> 00:07:22,150
"Where's his mother?"

241
00:07:22,160 --> 00:07:23,790
"Not in the picture."

242
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:25,590
"You got locked out how?"

243
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:27,430
"Family disagreement."

244
00:07:27,440 --> 00:07:29,190
"My parents' house.

245
00:07:29,200 --> 00:07:30,910
They told us to leave.

246
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:32,830
-15 out."

247
00:07:32,840 --> 00:07:34,230
He nodded.

248
00:07:34,240 --> 00:07:36,470
"Come on back. Break room."

249
00:07:36,480 --> 00:07:39,430
Couch, coffee maker, vending machine.

250
00:07:39,440 --> 00:07:41,430
He handed Connor a blanket.

251
00:07:41,440 --> 00:07:42,510
"Sit.

252
00:07:42,520 --> 00:07:43,950
I'll be back."

253
00:07:43,960 --> 00:07:45,750
Connor climbed on the couch, pulled the

254
00:07:45,760 --> 00:07:47,550
blanket over himself.

255
00:07:47,560 --> 00:07:49,830
Within minutes, he was asleep.

256
00:07:49,840 --> 00:07:52,150
Davies came back with a notepad.

257
00:07:52,160 --> 00:07:53,910
"Need some information.

258
00:07:53,920 --> 00:07:55,190
Full name?"

259
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:56,710
"Ethan Harrison."

260
00:07:56,720 --> 00:07:58,030
"Address?"

261
00:07:58,040 --> 00:08:00,070
"As of 2 hours ago, none."

262
00:08:00,080 --> 00:08:01,550
He wrote that down.

263
00:08:01,560 --> 00:08:03,190
"Previous address?"

264
00:08:03,200 --> 00:08:04,950
Gave him my parents' street.

265
00:08:04,960 --> 00:08:07,070
Explained in short sentences.

266
00:08:07,080 --> 00:08:08,790
"Lived there 2 months.

267
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:10,790
Tonight Connor broke something.

268
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:12,470
They told us to leave.

269
00:08:12,480 --> 00:08:13,790
Took my key."

270
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:15,270
Davies listened.

271
00:08:15,280 --> 00:08:16,830
When I finished, "You got somewhere

272
00:08:16,840 --> 00:08:17,950
tomorrow?"

273
00:08:17,960 --> 00:08:19,310
"I'll figure it out."

274
00:08:19,320 --> 00:08:20,790
He tapped his pen.

275
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:22,630
"Ethan, I'm calling this in. Child

276
00:08:22,640 --> 00:08:24,190
Protective Services."

277
00:08:24,200 --> 00:08:25,790
My stomach dropped.

278
00:08:25,800 --> 00:08:26,910
"Figured."

279
00:08:26,920 --> 00:08:28,350
"You're not upset?"

280
00:08:28,360 --> 00:08:29,750
"Kid's 6.

281
00:08:29,760 --> 00:08:30,910
Blizzard.

282
00:08:30,920 --> 00:08:32,310
You had to."

283
00:08:32,320 --> 00:08:33,550
He nodded.

284
00:08:33,560 --> 00:08:35,950
Stepped into the hall, made the call.

285
00:08:35,960 --> 00:08:37,830
Came back 5 minutes later.

286
00:08:37,840 --> 00:08:39,390
"Someone's coming.

287
00:08:39,400 --> 00:08:40,630
They're also sending a worker to your

288
00:08:40,640 --> 00:08:42,149
parents' address."

289
00:08:42,159 --> 00:08:43,350
"Tonight?"

290
00:08:43,360 --> 00:08:44,550
"Tonight.

291
00:08:44,560 --> 00:08:46,750
Weather emergency, minor child.

292
00:08:46,760 --> 00:08:48,390
They don't wait."

293
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:50,030
My chest tightened.

294
00:08:50,040 --> 00:08:52,030
My parents were going to lose it.

295
00:08:52,040 --> 00:08:53,710
An hour passed.

296
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:55,430
Connor slept hard.

297
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:58,430
I drank bad coffee, stared at my phone.

298
00:08:58,440 --> 00:09:00,390
18 missed calls.

299
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:02,630
Voicemails I didn't listen to.

300
00:09:02,640 --> 00:09:04,470
Text from my mother, "How dare you

301
00:09:04,480 --> 00:09:05,910
involve police?"

302
00:09:05,920 --> 00:09:07,510
I didn't respond.

303
00:09:07,520 --> 00:09:09,390
Put the phone face down.

304
00:09:09,400 --> 00:09:11,030
Davies' phone rang.

305
00:09:11,040 --> 00:09:13,790
He answered, listened, came back.

306
00:09:13,800 --> 00:09:15,590
"That was the case worker.

307
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:17,190
Janet Sims.

308
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:19,190
She just left your parents' place.

309
00:09:19,200 --> 00:09:20,790
Wants to talk to you.

310
00:09:20,800 --> 00:09:22,270
Speaker okay?"

311
00:09:22,280 --> 00:09:23,350
"Yeah."

312
00:09:23,360 --> 00:09:25,430
He dialed, hit speaker.

313
00:09:25,440 --> 00:09:26,830
A woman's voice came through,

314
00:09:26,840 --> 00:09:28,230
professional.

315
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:29,790
"Mr. Harrison?"

316
00:09:29,800 --> 00:09:31,110
"Yes, ma'am."

317
00:09:31,120 --> 00:09:34,350
"Janet Sims, Child Protective Services.

318
00:09:34,360 --> 00:09:35,990
Direct question.

319
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:37,510
Did you leave that house voluntarily

320
00:09:37,520 --> 00:09:38,590
tonight?"

321
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:39,950
"No, ma'am.

322
00:09:39,960 --> 00:09:42,310
They locked the door and took my key."

323
00:09:42,320 --> 00:09:44,350
"That matches what I observed.

324
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:46,550
Describe where you and Connor lived."

325
00:09:46,560 --> 00:09:47,830
"Guest room.

326
00:09:47,840 --> 00:09:50,670
Connor on an air mattress, me on a cot."

327
00:09:50,680 --> 00:09:52,230
"Your mother showed me a guest room full

328
00:09:52,240 --> 00:09:54,790
of boxes and your brother's belongings.

329
00:09:54,800 --> 00:09:56,110
No bed."

330
00:09:56,120 --> 00:09:57,590
"That's it.

331
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:59,670
We cleared floor space.

332
00:09:59,680 --> 00:10:01,030
Silence.

333
00:10:01,040 --> 00:10:03,870
Mr. Harrison, I'm opening a case.

334
00:10:03,880 --> 00:10:05,750
This is an unsafe eviction of a minor

335
00:10:05,760 --> 00:10:07,750
during weather emergency.

336
00:10:07,760 --> 00:10:10,070
I'm issuing an emergency motel voucher,

337
00:10:10,080 --> 00:10:11,590
three nights.

338
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:13,950
Officer Davies has details.

339
00:10:13,960 --> 00:10:15,190
Thank you.

340
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:17,110
Take care of your son.

341
00:10:17,120 --> 00:10:18,790
Line clicked off.

342
00:10:18,800 --> 00:10:21,470
Davies handed me a voucher and address.

343
00:10:21,480 --> 00:10:23,670
Motel six blocks away, prepaid through

344
00:10:23,680 --> 00:10:25,070
the weekend.

345
00:10:25,080 --> 00:10:26,670
You're set.

346
00:10:26,680 --> 00:10:29,230
I looked at Connor asleep on the couch.

347
00:10:29,240 --> 00:10:31,550
12 hours ago I had a family.

348
00:10:31,560 --> 00:10:34,030
Now I had a case number and a voucher.

349
00:10:34,040 --> 00:10:35,790
But Connor was warm,

350
00:10:35,800 --> 00:10:37,070
safe.

351
00:10:37,080 --> 00:10:38,750
That was enough.

352
00:10:38,760 --> 00:10:41,150
I picked him up, blanket and all.

353
00:10:41,160 --> 00:10:43,110
He barely stirred.

354
00:10:43,120 --> 00:10:44,910
Davies held the door.

355
00:10:44,920 --> 00:10:46,670
Drive safe.

356
00:10:46,680 --> 00:10:48,510
The blizzard was clearing.

357
00:10:48,520 --> 00:10:50,190
Snow lighter now.

358
00:10:50,200 --> 00:10:52,790
Sky starting to pale at the edges.

359
00:10:52,800 --> 00:10:55,230
I buckled Connor in, drove six blocks to

360
00:10:55,240 --> 00:10:57,470
a motel that wasn't great, but had heat

361
00:10:57,480 --> 00:10:59,190
and working locks.

362
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:00,590
Checked in.

363
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:02,670
Carried Connor to the room.

364
00:11:02,680 --> 00:11:05,110
Lay him on the bed still in his coat.

365
00:11:05,120 --> 00:11:07,270
He rolled over, grabbed his bear, didn't

366
00:11:07,280 --> 00:11:08,670
wake.

367
00:11:08,680 --> 00:11:10,190
I sat by the window and watched the

368
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:11,470
snow.

369
00:11:11,480 --> 00:11:13,030
Phone buzzed.

370
00:11:13,040 --> 00:11:14,550
More calls.

371
00:11:14,560 --> 00:11:16,150
I turned it off.

372
00:11:16,160 --> 00:11:17,829
Somewhere across town my parents were

373
00:11:17,839 --> 00:11:20,390
awake, furious, crafting their version

374
00:11:20,400 --> 00:11:21,630
where I was ungrateful and out of

375
00:11:21,640 --> 00:11:22,950
control.

376
00:11:22,960 --> 00:11:24,190
Let them.

377
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:25,550
I'd learned you can't control what

378
00:11:25,560 --> 00:11:27,030
people say.

379
00:11:27,040 --> 00:11:28,950
Only what you do next.

380
00:11:28,960 --> 00:11:30,910
And what I did next was make sure my son

381
00:11:30,920 --> 00:11:33,750
had a roof and heat and safety.

382
00:11:33,760 --> 00:11:35,670
Everything else could wait.

383
00:11:35,680 --> 00:11:37,230
Woke up in the motel to my phone

384
00:11:37,240 --> 00:11:39,750
vibrating itself off the nightstand.

385
00:11:39,760 --> 00:11:41,910
Connor was still asleep, sprawled across

386
00:11:41,920 --> 00:11:43,550
the bed with his bear tucked under one

387
00:11:43,560 --> 00:11:44,670
arm.

388
00:11:44,680 --> 00:11:46,310
Picked up the phone.

389
00:11:46,320 --> 00:11:48,350
18 missed calls.

390
00:11:48,360 --> 00:11:50,110
All from my parents number, my mother's

391
00:11:50,120 --> 00:11:51,750
cell, two from numbers I didn't

392
00:11:51,760 --> 00:11:53,230
recognize.

393
00:11:53,240 --> 00:11:55,070
Checked voicemails.

394
00:11:55,080 --> 00:11:56,710
Put it on speaker low so Connor wouldn't

395
00:11:56,720 --> 00:11:57,870
hear.

396
00:11:57,880 --> 00:11:59,870
First one, my mother.

397
00:11:59,880 --> 00:12:01,710
Ethan, call us.

398
00:12:01,720 --> 00:12:03,630
We need to talk about this.

399
00:12:03,640 --> 00:12:05,910
Second one, hour later.

400
00:12:05,920 --> 00:12:07,550
Her voice tighter.

401
00:12:07,560 --> 00:12:08,910
I don't know what you told those people,

402
00:12:08,920 --> 00:12:10,950
but you need to fix this.

403
00:12:10,960 --> 00:12:13,110
Third one, my father.

404
00:12:13,120 --> 00:12:14,350
You involved the state in family

405
00:12:14,360 --> 00:12:17,030
business. That's unforgivable.

406
00:12:17,040 --> 00:12:20,270
Fourth one, my mother again, crying now.

407
00:12:20,280 --> 00:12:22,110
How could you do this to us? After

408
00:12:22,120 --> 00:12:24,310
everything we've done for you.

409
00:12:24,320 --> 00:12:26,110
I deleted them all.

410
00:12:26,120 --> 00:12:28,230
Put the phone on silent.

411
00:12:28,240 --> 00:12:31,030
Connor stirred, opened his eyes.

412
00:12:31,040 --> 00:12:32,470
Where are we?

413
00:12:32,480 --> 00:12:33,870
Motel.

414
00:12:33,880 --> 00:12:35,390
We're safe.

415
00:12:35,400 --> 00:12:37,230
He sat up, looked around the room like

416
00:12:37,240 --> 00:12:39,390
he was checking if it was real.

417
00:12:39,400 --> 00:12:40,990
Can we stay here?

418
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:42,670
For a couple days.

419
00:12:42,680 --> 00:12:44,870
Then we'll figure out next steps.

420
00:12:44,880 --> 00:12:46,230
He nodded.

421
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:48,390
Didn't ask about my parents.

422
00:12:48,400 --> 00:12:50,510
Didn't ask when we were going home.

423
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:52,190
Six years old and already learning that

424
00:12:52,200 --> 00:12:54,710
home wasn't a place you could count on.

425
00:12:54,720 --> 00:12:56,990
Two days later, Janet called.

426
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:58,870
I was at a gas station buying food with

427
00:12:58,880 --> 00:13:01,150
what was left of my cash. Connor in the

428
00:13:01,160 --> 00:13:03,790
backseat eating a pack of crackers.

429
00:13:03,800 --> 00:13:06,670
Mr. Harrison, this is Janet Sims.

430
00:13:06,680 --> 00:13:08,190
Do you have a minute?

431
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:09,310
Yeah.

432
00:13:09,320 --> 00:13:11,590
I've completed initial interviews.

433
00:13:11,600 --> 00:13:13,230
Your parents, your brother Kyle in

434
00:13:13,240 --> 00:13:15,950
Boston, and a neighbor, Mrs. Chen, who

435
00:13:15,960 --> 00:13:18,190
lives next door to your parents.

436
00:13:18,200 --> 00:13:19,390
Okay.

437
00:13:19,400 --> 00:13:22,030
Mrs. Chen corroborated your account.

438
00:13:22,040 --> 00:13:24,030
She heard yelling that night, saw you

439
00:13:24,040 --> 00:13:26,230
and Connor leave with bags, noted the

440
00:13:26,240 --> 00:13:28,470
time and weather conditions.

441
00:13:28,480 --> 00:13:30,070
Your brother stated he wasn't present,

442
00:13:30,080 --> 00:13:32,910
but confirmed ongoing family tension.

443
00:13:32,920 --> 00:13:35,870
Your parents deny forcing you to leave.

444
00:13:35,880 --> 00:13:38,150
They took my key and locked the door.

445
00:13:38,160 --> 00:13:39,990
I know. The evidence supports your

446
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:41,950
version. The case is staying open

447
00:13:41,960 --> 00:13:43,430
pending a home visit and follow-up

448
00:13:43,440 --> 00:13:44,990
interview with you.

449
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:46,630
Home visit where?

450
00:13:46,640 --> 00:13:49,390
I don't have a home. We'll work on that.

451
00:13:49,400 --> 00:13:51,710
I'll call you early next week.

452
00:13:51,720 --> 00:13:53,190
She hung up.

453
00:13:53,200 --> 00:13:55,750
I sat in the car staring at my phone.

454
00:13:55,760 --> 00:13:58,150
My parents had lied to CPS. Straight up

455
00:13:58,160 --> 00:13:59,990
denied what they'd done.

456
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:01,910
Part of me was surprised.

457
00:14:01,920 --> 00:14:03,790
Most of me wasn't.

458
00:14:03,800 --> 00:14:06,590
Next morning, email notification.

459
00:14:06,600 --> 00:14:08,710
Sender I didn't recognize.

460
00:14:08,720 --> 00:14:09,990
Opened it.

461
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:11,510
Subject line.

462
00:14:11,520 --> 00:14:13,550
Cease and desist on behalf of Richard

463
00:14:13,560 --> 00:14:15,350
and Carol Harrison.

464
00:14:15,360 --> 00:14:16,670
Skimmed it.

465
00:14:16,680 --> 00:14:19,190
Legal letterhead, family attorney,

466
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:21,069
language about defamation and filing

467
00:14:21,079 --> 00:14:23,390
false reports and potential civil action

468
00:14:23,400 --> 00:14:25,230
if I continued to spread malicious lies

469
00:14:25,240 --> 00:14:27,270
about my parents character.

470
00:14:27,280 --> 00:14:28,870
My hands shook.

471
00:14:28,880 --> 00:14:30,430
Not from fear.

472
00:14:30,440 --> 00:14:32,670
From rage. Forwarded it to Janet with

473
00:14:32,680 --> 00:14:34,150
one line.

474
00:14:34,160 --> 00:14:35,470
Got this today.

475
00:14:35,480 --> 00:14:37,190
Thought you should see.

476
00:14:37,200 --> 00:14:39,310
She called 20 minutes later.

477
00:14:39,320 --> 00:14:40,710
Ignore it.

478
00:14:40,720 --> 00:14:42,670
They're threatening to sue me.

479
00:14:42,680 --> 00:14:44,470
For telling the truth.

480
00:14:44,480 --> 00:14:46,470
That's not defamation.

481
00:14:46,480 --> 00:14:49,110
Truth is an absolute defense.

482
00:14:49,120 --> 00:14:50,990
They're trying to scare you.

483
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:52,430
It's working.

484
00:14:52,440 --> 00:14:53,710
Don't let it.

485
00:14:53,720 --> 00:14:55,750
Stay focused on Connor.

486
00:14:55,760 --> 00:14:57,390
I'll handle this.

487
00:14:57,400 --> 00:14:58,949
I tried to.

488
00:14:58,959 --> 00:15:00,510
But focus was hard when I got the next

489
00:15:00,520 --> 00:15:02,310
call an hour later.

490
00:15:02,320 --> 00:15:04,750
My supervisor from the warehouse.

491
00:15:04,760 --> 00:15:06,790
Ethan, where are you?

492
00:15:06,800 --> 00:15:09,069
You were scheduled 6:00 a.m.

493
00:15:09,079 --> 00:15:10,790
My brain blanked.

494
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:13,190
I'd completely forgotten my shift.

495
00:15:13,200 --> 00:15:14,870
Between the lockout and CPS and the

496
00:15:14,880 --> 00:15:16,790
motel and everything, work had fallen

497
00:15:16,800 --> 00:15:19,150
off my mental radar entirely.

498
00:15:19,160 --> 00:15:21,470
Family emergency, I said.

499
00:15:21,480 --> 00:15:24,949
My son, we had to. I can explain.

500
00:15:24,959 --> 00:15:26,949
This is your third no call, no show this

501
00:15:26,959 --> 00:15:28,069
month.

502
00:15:28,079 --> 00:15:29,990
I was laid off. You hired me back

503
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:32,270
part-time 3 weeks ago. And you've missed

504
00:15:32,280 --> 00:15:34,430
three shifts without calling in.

505
00:15:34,440 --> 00:15:36,069
I can't keep doing this. You're

506
00:15:36,079 --> 00:15:38,430
terminated effective immediately.

507
00:15:38,440 --> 00:15:40,069
The line went dead.

508
00:15:40,079 --> 00:15:41,870
I sat in the motel parking lot with the

509
00:15:41,880 --> 00:15:43,870
engine off and the heat fading and tried

510
00:15:43,880 --> 00:15:45,310
to figure out how this had all fallen

511
00:15:45,320 --> 00:15:47,030
apart so fast.

512
00:15:47,040 --> 00:15:50,470
72 hours ago I had a roof and a job.

513
00:15:50,480 --> 00:15:52,150
Now I had neither.

514
00:15:52,160 --> 00:15:54,069
Connor was inside watching cartoons on

515
00:15:54,079 --> 00:15:55,670
the motel TV.

516
00:15:55,680 --> 00:15:57,110
Didn't know his dad had just lost the

517
00:15:57,120 --> 00:15:58,990
only income we had.

518
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:01,510
That night Connor woke up screaming.

519
00:16:01,520 --> 00:16:03,390
I bolted upright, reached for him in the

520
00:16:03,400 --> 00:16:04,670
dark.

521
00:16:04,680 --> 00:16:07,069
You're okay. You're okay, I said,

522
00:16:07,079 --> 00:16:08,790
pulling him close.

523
00:16:08,800 --> 00:16:10,550
Just a dream.

524
00:16:10,560 --> 00:16:13,069
He was shaking, gasping.

525
00:16:13,079 --> 00:16:14,710
They locked the door.

526
00:16:14,720 --> 00:16:16,270
I couldn't get in.

527
00:16:16,280 --> 00:16:17,910
It was cold.

528
00:16:17,920 --> 00:16:19,949
We're not there anymore, buddy.

529
00:16:19,959 --> 00:16:21,550
We're safe.

530
00:16:21,560 --> 00:16:23,350
He cried into my shoulder for 10 minutes

531
00:16:23,360 --> 00:16:25,510
before falling back asleep.

532
00:16:25,520 --> 00:16:26,910
I stayed awake the rest of the night

533
00:16:26,920 --> 00:16:28,630
watching him breathe.

534
00:16:28,640 --> 00:16:30,870
Next afternoon my phone rang.

535
00:16:30,880 --> 00:16:32,430
Unknown number.

536
00:16:32,440 --> 00:16:33,590
Normally I wouldn't answer, but

537
00:16:33,600 --> 00:16:35,390
something made me pick up.

538
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:38,630
Ethan? Kyle? My younger brother.

539
00:16:38,640 --> 00:16:41,069
Harvard Law, golden child. The one who'd

540
00:16:41,079 --> 00:16:43,270
gotten out and never looked back.

541
00:16:43,280 --> 00:16:44,430
Yeah.

542
00:16:44,440 --> 00:16:46,110
What on earth, man?

543
00:16:46,120 --> 00:16:48,310
Mom called me crying saying CPS showed

544
00:16:48,320 --> 00:16:51,150
up. Dad's talking about lawyers.

545
00:16:51,160 --> 00:16:53,350
What's going on? I explained, short

546
00:16:53,360 --> 00:16:56,430
version. Trophy, lockout, blizzard,

547
00:16:56,440 --> 00:16:58,829
police station, CPS.

548
00:16:58,839 --> 00:17:01,590
Silence on his end for a long moment.

549
00:17:01,600 --> 00:17:02,470
Then,

550
00:17:02,480 --> 00:17:04,630
Dad said you attacked him.

551
00:17:04,640 --> 00:17:06,230
And you believed him?

552
00:17:06,240 --> 00:17:07,750
More silence.

553
00:17:07,760 --> 00:17:10,069
I didn't attack anyone, I said.

554
00:17:10,079 --> 00:17:12,669
Connor accidentally broke a trophy. They

555
00:17:12,679 --> 00:17:14,829
kicked us out during a blizzard.

556
00:17:14,839 --> 00:17:16,350
That's it.

557
00:17:16,360 --> 00:17:18,030
Kyle exhaled.

558
00:17:18,040 --> 00:17:20,750
Mom said you manipulated the police.

559
00:17:20,760 --> 00:17:22,270
I drove to a police station and said we

560
00:17:22,280 --> 00:17:23,829
got locked out.

561
00:17:23,839 --> 00:17:25,429
That's not manipulation. That's

562
00:17:25,439 --> 00:17:26,949
survival.

563
00:17:26,959 --> 00:17:28,630
Why didn't you call me?

564
00:17:28,640 --> 00:17:30,070
You moved to Boston to get away from

565
00:17:30,080 --> 00:17:32,950
this family, Kyle. Why would I call?

566
00:17:32,960 --> 00:17:34,669
He didn't answer that.

567
00:17:34,679 --> 00:17:36,630
Look, I don't know what to believe.

568
00:17:36,640 --> 00:17:38,270
Believe what you want.

569
00:17:38,280 --> 00:17:40,470
I've got enough to deal with.

570
00:17:40,480 --> 00:17:41,870
I hung up.

571
00:17:41,880 --> 00:17:44,630
Felt bad about it for maybe 5 seconds.

572
00:17:44,640 --> 00:17:46,190
Then moved on.

573
00:17:46,200 --> 00:17:48,950
The motel voucher ran out on day three.

574
00:17:48,960 --> 00:17:50,870
Janet called that morning.

575
00:17:50,880 --> 00:17:53,310
I found emergency housing. Transitional

576
00:17:53,320 --> 00:17:55,430
shelter for single parents.

577
00:17:55,440 --> 00:17:56,950
It's not permanent, but it's safe and

578
00:17:56,960 --> 00:17:58,870
warm and supervised.

579
00:17:58,880 --> 00:18:00,910
My pride tried to fight it.

580
00:18:00,920 --> 00:18:02,790
I don't need charity. Connor needs

581
00:18:02,800 --> 00:18:04,870
stable housing. This gets you both

582
00:18:04,880 --> 00:18:06,830
stable while you find work. There's a

583
00:18:06,840 --> 00:18:08,910
bed for him, a cot for you, shared

584
00:18:08,920 --> 00:18:11,550
kitchen, case management support.

585
00:18:11,560 --> 00:18:13,510
I closed my eyes.

586
00:18:13,520 --> 00:18:16,550
Okay. She texted me the address.

587
00:18:16,560 --> 00:18:18,550
I packed our two duffel bags, checked

588
00:18:18,560 --> 00:18:20,470
out, drove across town to a low brick

589
00:18:20,480 --> 00:18:22,350
building with a sign that said Family

590
00:18:22,360 --> 00:18:23,630
Haven.

591
00:18:23,640 --> 00:18:27,190
Inside, small rooms, clean but worn.

592
00:18:27,200 --> 00:18:29,430
Met the director, signed paperwork, got

593
00:18:29,440 --> 00:18:31,070
assigned a room.

594
00:18:31,080 --> 00:18:33,149
Two other single dads living there, one

595
00:18:33,159 --> 00:18:34,750
with a toddler, one with twin

596
00:18:34,760 --> 00:18:36,270
8-year-olds.

597
00:18:36,280 --> 00:18:37,950
They nodded when we walked in, didn't

598
00:18:37,960 --> 00:18:39,550
ask questions.

599
00:18:39,560 --> 00:18:41,390
Connor got a narrow bed with a donated

600
00:18:41,400 --> 00:18:42,750
comforter.

601
00:18:42,760 --> 00:18:44,270
I got a cot.

602
00:18:44,280 --> 00:18:46,909
Our stuff fit in one closet.

603
00:18:46,919 --> 00:18:48,750
You'll be okay here, one of the dads

604
00:18:48,760 --> 00:18:49,870
said.

605
00:18:49,880 --> 00:18:53,149
Jerome, mid-30s, kind eyes.

606
00:18:53,159 --> 00:18:55,190
His son was three, playing with blocks

607
00:18:55,200 --> 00:18:56,630
in the corner.

608
00:18:56,640 --> 00:18:58,590
We all been where you are.

609
00:18:58,600 --> 00:18:59,870
Thanks.

610
00:18:59,880 --> 00:19:01,790
That evening I was in the shared kitchen

611
00:19:01,800 --> 00:19:03,350
making mac and cheese from the food

612
00:19:03,360 --> 00:19:04,870
pantry when someone knocked on the front

613
00:19:04,880 --> 00:19:06,070
door.

614
00:19:06,080 --> 00:19:07,790
Director answered.

615
00:19:07,800 --> 00:19:09,790
I heard my mother's voice.

616
00:19:09,800 --> 00:19:12,149
I need to speak to my son. Ma'am,

617
00:19:12,159 --> 00:19:14,270
residents have to approve visitors.

618
00:19:14,280 --> 00:19:15,990
The director came to find me. Your

619
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:18,230
mother's here. I don't want to see her.

620
00:19:18,240 --> 00:19:20,190
She's asking to talk to you. I can tell

621
00:19:20,200 --> 00:19:21,590
her to leave.

622
00:19:21,600 --> 00:19:22,990
I'll handle it.

623
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:24,790
Went to the front lobby.

624
00:19:24,800 --> 00:19:26,870
My mother stood there in her coat, face

625
00:19:26,880 --> 00:19:28,750
blotchy from crying.

626
00:19:28,760 --> 00:19:31,590
She saw me and her expression crumpled.

627
00:19:31,600 --> 00:19:34,190
Ethan, please. Can we talk? What's there

628
00:19:34,200 --> 00:19:35,669
to talk about?

629
00:19:35,679 --> 00:19:37,550
I need you to come home. This has gone

630
00:19:37,560 --> 00:19:38,909
too far.

631
00:19:38,919 --> 00:19:41,710
CPS, lawyers, you living in a shelter,

632
00:19:41,720 --> 00:19:44,550
it's insane. You kicked us out.

633
00:19:44,560 --> 00:19:46,550
We were angry. People say things when

634
00:19:46,560 --> 00:19:47,990
they're angry.

635
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:50,070
You called Connor trash.

636
00:19:50,080 --> 00:19:51,590
I didn't mean it.

637
00:19:51,600 --> 00:19:53,070
You meant it.

638
00:19:53,080 --> 00:19:54,870
Her face hardened.

639
00:19:54,880 --> 00:19:56,670
You're punishing us.

640
00:19:56,680 --> 00:19:58,070
You know that?

641
00:19:58,080 --> 00:20:00,710
You're using Connor to punish us.

642
00:20:00,720 --> 00:20:02,390
I stared at her.

643
00:20:02,400 --> 00:20:03,750
You locked a 6-year-old out in a

644
00:20:03,760 --> 00:20:05,150
blizzard and I'm the one punishing

645
00:20:05,160 --> 00:20:06,310
people?

646
00:20:06,320 --> 00:20:07,830
If you would just apologize and come

647
00:20:07,840 --> 00:20:09,950
back, we could fix this.

648
00:20:09,960 --> 00:20:11,990
Apologize for what?

649
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:13,910
For involving the police.

650
00:20:13,920 --> 00:20:16,470
For making us look like monsters.

651
00:20:16,480 --> 00:20:19,110
I turned around and walked back inside.

652
00:20:19,120 --> 00:20:21,630
She called after me, but I didn't stop.

653
00:20:21,640 --> 00:20:23,990
Director locked the door behind me.

654
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:25,190
You good?

655
00:20:25,200 --> 00:20:26,550
Yeah.

656
00:20:26,560 --> 00:20:28,670
Few days later, Janet scheduled a formal

657
00:20:28,680 --> 00:20:29,830
interview.

658
00:20:29,840 --> 00:20:31,510
Came to the shelter, sat with me in a

659
00:20:31,520 --> 00:20:33,830
small office, notepad out.

660
00:20:33,840 --> 00:20:35,310
I need to ask about your history with

661
00:20:35,320 --> 00:20:38,110
your parents. Pattern of behavior?

662
00:20:38,120 --> 00:20:40,190
Prior to the lockout, were there other

663
00:20:40,200 --> 00:20:41,510
incidents?

664
00:20:41,520 --> 00:20:43,750
I thought about lying. Making it sound

665
00:20:43,760 --> 00:20:45,350
better than it was.

666
00:20:45,360 --> 00:20:47,030
Then thought about Connor waking up

667
00:20:47,040 --> 00:20:49,270
screaming about locked doors.

668
00:20:49,280 --> 00:20:50,950
Told her the truth.

669
00:20:50,960 --> 00:20:53,550
They forgot Connor's birthday twice.

670
00:20:53,560 --> 00:20:55,190
Refused to babysit so I could work

671
00:20:55,200 --> 00:20:56,670
evening shifts.

672
00:20:56,680 --> 00:20:58,990
Called him a mistake regularly.

673
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:00,830
Made it clear we were tolerated, not

674
00:21:00,840 --> 00:21:01,950
wanted.

675
00:21:01,960 --> 00:21:04,390
Compared him to Kyle constantly.

676
00:21:04,400 --> 00:21:06,150
When I lost my job, they let me stay,

677
00:21:06,160 --> 00:21:08,670
but reminded me daily it was charity.

678
00:21:08,680 --> 00:21:10,470
Janet wrote it all down.

679
00:21:10,480 --> 00:21:12,310
How long were you living there?

680
00:21:12,320 --> 00:21:13,670
2 months.

681
00:21:13,680 --> 00:21:15,190
And before that?

682
00:21:15,200 --> 00:21:17,030
Apartment across town.

683
00:21:17,040 --> 00:21:18,830
Lost it when I got laid off, couldn't

684
00:21:18,840 --> 00:21:20,030
make rent.

685
00:21:20,040 --> 00:21:23,350
Support system, friends, other family?

686
00:21:23,360 --> 00:21:24,670
Not really.

687
00:21:24,680 --> 00:21:27,470
My ex, Connor's mom, left when he was 6

688
00:21:27,480 --> 00:21:29,030
months old. Haven't heard from her

689
00:21:29,040 --> 00:21:30,230
since.

690
00:21:30,240 --> 00:21:31,910
Friends kind of faded after I became a

691
00:21:31,920 --> 00:21:33,350
single dad.

692
00:21:33,360 --> 00:21:35,310
She closed her notepad.

693
00:21:35,320 --> 00:21:37,190
This will be in my report.

694
00:21:37,200 --> 00:21:38,630
Will it matter?

695
00:21:38,640 --> 00:21:40,710
It establishes a pattern.

696
00:21:40,720 --> 00:21:43,830
It shows the lockout wasn't isolated.

697
00:21:43,840 --> 00:21:45,870
That night my phone rang.

698
00:21:45,880 --> 00:21:47,750
Unknown number again.

699
00:21:47,760 --> 00:21:49,550
I almost didn't answer.

700
00:21:49,560 --> 00:21:51,110
Then did.

701
00:21:51,120 --> 00:21:53,990
My father's voice, loud and sharp.

702
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:55,950
You destroyed this family?

703
00:21:55,960 --> 00:21:57,950
I locked out a 6-year-old in a blizzard,

704
00:21:57,960 --> 00:21:59,110
I said.

705
00:21:59,120 --> 00:22:00,550
That was you.

706
00:22:00,560 --> 00:22:02,350
You involved the state.

707
00:22:02,360 --> 00:22:04,510
You made us look like abusers.

708
00:22:04,520 --> 00:22:06,390
You are abusers.

709
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:08,150
He started yelling, something about

710
00:22:08,160 --> 00:22:10,110
disrespect and ingratitude and poisoning

711
00:22:10,120 --> 00:22:11,710
Kyle against them.

712
00:22:11,720 --> 00:22:14,350
I hung up. Blocked the number.

713
00:22:14,360 --> 00:22:16,630
Connor was watching from his bed.

714
00:22:16,640 --> 00:22:18,310
Was that grandpa?

715
00:22:18,320 --> 00:22:19,470
Yeah.

716
00:22:19,480 --> 00:22:21,190
Is he still mad?

717
00:22:21,200 --> 00:22:22,630
Yeah, buddy.

718
00:22:22,640 --> 00:22:23,910
He is.

719
00:22:23,920 --> 00:22:26,510
Connor rolled over, faced the wall.

720
00:22:26,520 --> 00:22:27,750
Okay.

721
00:22:27,760 --> 00:22:29,950
3 weeks after the lockout, I got hired

722
00:22:29,960 --> 00:22:31,669
at an auto parts store.

723
00:22:31,679 --> 00:22:34,830
$16 an hour, 35 hours a week.

724
00:22:34,840 --> 00:22:37,030
Not great, but real.

725
00:22:37,040 --> 00:22:39,950
Manager asked why I left my last job.

726
00:22:39,960 --> 00:22:41,630
I told the truth.

727
00:22:41,640 --> 00:22:44,510
Family emergency, missed shifts.

728
00:22:44,520 --> 00:22:46,430
He paused, then said,

729
00:22:46,440 --> 00:22:48,070
When can you start?

730
00:22:48,080 --> 00:22:49,510
The next day.

731
00:22:49,520 --> 00:22:52,150
First paycheck came 2 weeks later.

732
00:22:52,160 --> 00:22:54,870
$560 after tax.

733
00:22:54,880 --> 00:22:57,630
Shelter charged 200 a month, subsidized

734
00:22:57,640 --> 00:22:58,630
rate.

735
00:22:58,640 --> 00:23:01,550
Left me 360 for food, bus fare,

736
00:23:01,560 --> 00:23:03,230
everything else.

737
00:23:03,240 --> 00:23:05,070
I sat on my cot that night and looked at

738
00:23:05,080 --> 00:23:06,750
the deposit slip.

739
00:23:06,760 --> 00:23:09,190
3 weeks ago, we were homeless.

740
00:23:09,200 --> 00:23:11,550
Now we had $700 in the bank and a

741
00:23:11,560 --> 00:23:14,030
paycheck coming every 2 weeks.

742
00:23:14,040 --> 00:23:16,230
Connor was asleep, finally sleeping

743
00:23:16,240 --> 00:23:18,430
through the night without nightmares.

744
00:23:18,440 --> 00:23:20,070
It wasn't much.

745
00:23:20,080 --> 00:23:21,669
But it was ours.

746
00:23:21,679 --> 00:23:23,510
And that was enough.

747
00:23:23,520 --> 00:23:25,710
Month after the lockout, life found a

748
00:23:25,720 --> 00:23:26,870
rhythm.

749
00:23:26,880 --> 00:23:29,950
Auto parts store 5 days a week, 8-hour

750
00:23:29,960 --> 00:23:31,870
shifts, stocking shelves and running

751
00:23:31,880 --> 00:23:33,110
register.

752
00:23:33,120 --> 00:23:35,150
Came home to the shelter, made dinner in

753
00:23:35,160 --> 00:23:36,669
the shared kitchen with Jerome and the

754
00:23:36,679 --> 00:23:38,910
other dads, helped Connor with homework

755
00:23:38,920 --> 00:23:40,990
at the small table in our room.

756
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:43,510
Connor's teacher, Mrs. Patterson, sent

757
00:23:43,520 --> 00:23:45,390
encouraging emails.

758
00:23:45,400 --> 00:23:48,310
He's doing well. Participating more.

759
00:23:48,320 --> 00:23:50,190
Let me know if you need anything. Small

760
00:23:50,200 --> 00:23:51,750
kindnesses from people who owed me

761
00:23:51,760 --> 00:23:52,910
nothing.

762
00:23:52,920 --> 00:23:55,390
Evenings I did math on napkins.

763
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:59,030
Current savings, $1,247.

764
00:23:59,040 --> 00:24:01,310
Rent deposits around here, first month

765
00:24:01,320 --> 00:24:04,870
plus security, averaged $1,900 minimum.

766
00:24:04,880 --> 00:24:07,870
At my current save rate, 5 months.

767
00:24:07,880 --> 00:24:09,430
Maybe four if I picked up weekend

768
00:24:09,440 --> 00:24:10,590
overtime.

769
00:24:10,600 --> 00:24:12,470
Unless something changed.

770
00:24:12,480 --> 00:24:14,750
Something changed on a Tuesday.

771
00:24:14,760 --> 00:24:16,510
I was restocking oil filters when

772
00:24:16,520 --> 00:24:18,430
someone walked into the store.

773
00:24:18,440 --> 00:24:19,950
Looked up.

774
00:24:19,960 --> 00:24:21,470
My brother Kyle stood there in a

775
00:24:21,480 --> 00:24:23,470
button-down and jeans, looking out of

776
00:24:23,480 --> 00:24:25,070
place among the motor oil and tire

777
00:24:25,080 --> 00:24:26,350
displays.

778
00:24:26,360 --> 00:24:27,870
Stared at him.

779
00:24:27,880 --> 00:24:30,430
What are you doing here? Can we talk?

780
00:24:30,440 --> 00:24:31,990
After your shift?

781
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:33,590
I'm off at 5.

782
00:24:33,600 --> 00:24:35,030
I'll wait.

783
00:24:35,040 --> 00:24:36,990
He sat in his car in the parking lot for

784
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:38,510
2 hours.

785
00:24:38,520 --> 00:24:40,190
I watched him through the window between

786
00:24:40,200 --> 00:24:41,990
customers, trying to figure out what he

787
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:43,150
wanted.

788
00:24:43,160 --> 00:24:44,790
5:00 hit.

789
00:24:44,800 --> 00:24:46,230
Clocked out.

790
00:24:46,240 --> 00:24:47,990
Met him outside.

791
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:49,790
There's a coffee shop down the block, he

792
00:24:49,800 --> 00:24:50,910
said.

793
00:24:50,920 --> 00:24:52,310
Fine.

794
00:24:52,320 --> 00:24:54,230
We walked in silence.

795
00:24:54,240 --> 00:24:57,190
Ordered coffee, sat in a corner booth.

796
00:24:57,200 --> 00:24:58,990
Kyle looks tired.

797
00:24:59,000 --> 00:25:00,990
Not just physical tired.

798
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:02,910
The kind that goes deeper.

799
00:25:02,920 --> 00:25:05,430
I talked to Mrs. Chen, he said.

800
00:25:05,440 --> 00:25:06,790
The neighbor.

801
00:25:06,800 --> 00:25:09,030
She told me what she heard that night.

802
00:25:09,040 --> 00:25:10,310
The yelling.

803
00:25:10,320 --> 00:25:12,470
Seeing you leave with bags.

804
00:25:12,480 --> 00:25:13,870
The weather.

805
00:25:13,880 --> 00:25:15,110
Okay.

806
00:25:15,120 --> 00:25:17,030
Dad said you were lying.

807
00:25:17,040 --> 00:25:18,470
That you left on your own and made up

808
00:25:18,480 --> 00:25:20,230
the lockout story.

809
00:25:20,240 --> 00:25:22,150
And you believed him.

810
00:25:22,160 --> 00:25:24,150
Kyle looked at his coffee.

811
00:25:24,160 --> 00:25:25,950
Because it was easier.

812
00:25:25,960 --> 00:25:27,350
I waited.

813
00:25:27,360 --> 00:25:28,630
Because I didn't want to admit our

814
00:25:28,640 --> 00:25:31,150
parents are, he paused, searching for

815
00:25:31,160 --> 00:25:32,310
the word.

816
00:25:32,320 --> 00:25:34,430
Jerks? I finished.

817
00:25:34,440 --> 00:25:35,790
He nodded.

818
00:25:35,800 --> 00:25:36,950
Yeah.

819
00:25:36,960 --> 00:25:38,350
That.

820
00:25:38,360 --> 00:25:40,430
We sat quiet for a minute.

821
00:25:40,440 --> 00:25:42,390
Then he pulled out his phone, opened his

822
00:25:42,400 --> 00:25:44,790
banking app, turned it toward me.

823
00:25:44,800 --> 00:25:46,910
I can give you 800. It's what I can

824
00:25:46,920 --> 00:25:48,350
spare right now.

825
00:25:48,360 --> 00:25:50,669
My pride kicked in automatic.

826
00:25:50,679 --> 00:25:53,750
I don't need charity. It's not charity.

827
00:25:53,760 --> 00:25:55,750
Kyle's voice was firm.

828
00:25:55,760 --> 00:25:58,270
It's me fixing what I didn't stop.

829
00:25:58,280 --> 00:25:59,710
I wasn't there that night, but I've been

830
00:25:59,720 --> 00:26:01,550
there for 22 years watching them treat

831
00:26:01,560 --> 00:26:02,750
you different.

832
00:26:02,760 --> 00:26:04,150
I knew it was happening and I left

833
00:26:04,160 --> 00:26:05,390
anyway.

834
00:26:05,400 --> 00:26:06,950
So take the money.

835
00:26:06,960 --> 00:26:08,669
Stared at him.

836
00:26:08,679 --> 00:26:11,150
Kyle had never stood up to our parents.

837
00:26:11,160 --> 00:26:13,750
Not once. I'll pay you back.

838
00:26:13,760 --> 00:26:14,990
I know.

839
00:26:15,000 --> 00:26:17,150
He transferred it right there.

840
00:26:17,160 --> 00:26:19,710
My phone buzzed with the notification.

841
00:26:19,720 --> 00:26:21,510
$800.

842
00:26:21,520 --> 00:26:24,030
That night I sat on my cot and counted.

843
00:26:24,040 --> 00:26:26,669
Savings, 1247.

844
00:26:26,679 --> 00:26:28,950
Kyle's money, 800.

845
00:26:28,960 --> 00:26:31,190
Total, 2047.

846
00:26:31,200 --> 00:26:32,910
Enough for first month and deposit at

847
00:26:32,920 --> 00:26:34,350
most places.

848
00:26:34,360 --> 00:26:36,590
Not all, but most.

849
00:26:36,600 --> 00:26:38,190
Connor was reading a book Jerome had

850
00:26:38,200 --> 00:26:39,310
given him.

851
00:26:39,320 --> 00:26:40,550
Looked up.

852
00:26:40,560 --> 00:26:42,310
Why are you smiling?

853
00:26:42,320 --> 00:26:44,310
We're getting our own place, buddy.

854
00:26:44,320 --> 00:26:45,990
His face lit up.

855
00:26:46,000 --> 00:26:47,110
Really?

856
00:26:47,120 --> 00:26:48,550
Really.

857
00:26:48,560 --> 00:26:50,790
Few days later, Kyle called me.

858
00:26:50,800 --> 00:26:52,150
Voice tight.

859
00:26:52,160 --> 00:26:53,950
I told them, he said.

860
00:26:53,960 --> 00:26:55,430
Mom and Dad.

861
00:26:55,440 --> 00:26:57,110
That I gave you money.

862
